I have a complaint against U.S. Bank XXXX. I noticed I was overdrawn XXXX. I immediately deposited XXXX which brought up account balance to a little over XXXX. Then they still going to charge me an overdraft charge. Why? The account was n't overdrawn at that time ...? Seems they are mad because I got the account back up before they had the chance to charge me, but chose to do so anyway. I want my XXXX back. How dare they pull such shady practices. Most banks give you XXXX free overdraft, this was my fIrst XXXX. Please help me as banks should not be able to pull such bogus deals. 

I want my XXXX refunded. 

































XXXX {$20.00} - {$4.00} XXXX/XXXX/2016 XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX Ia {$6.00} {$15.00}
